The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 10: Gold prices fell sharply to a three-month low on the back of sustained selling by stockists and weak overseas trend, ending at a loss of Rs 50 at Rs 9,180 per 10 gram. Trading activity was also affected because of a lean season in terms of marriages and festivals. Moreover, fresh arrivals created an adequate stocks position. The prices had fallen to such a level on April 18.

 New Delhi, June 10: Matrix Laboratories has reported a 27.57 per cent rise in consolidated net profit at Rs 36.2 crore for the quarter ended March 2006 against Rs 28.6 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago. The company?s consolidated sales during the quarter rose to Rs 392.8 crore. In the previous fiscal, Matrix Laboratories had registered standalone sales of Rs 158.4 crore.

 New Delhi, June 10: Sebi chairman M. Damodaran today inaugurated a new office of the market regulator here.Sebi has three regional offices in Chennai, Calcutta and New Delhi.




